#AAMI Insurance Portal - User Registration Web Interface
Tech Demo: Secure User Sign-up Flow with PHP + MySQL
This project delivers a production-ready web interface for inserting new user records into the users table of the AAMI insurance portal database. 
Perfect for demonstrating full-stack LAMP development, form validation, and secure database insertion.
##Project Focus
- Target Table: users (core table for insurance portal sign-ups)
- Core Functionality: HTML form → PHP validation → MySQL insertion
- Use Case: Customer onboarding with username, email, phone, subscription, and payment plan capture
##Tech Stack
- Web Server: XAMPP (Apache + MariaDB/MySQL + PHP)
- Database: MySQL (MariaDB)
- Backend: PHP (form processing + SQL insertion)
- Frontend: HTML5 + CSS3 (responsive form)
- Tools: phpMyAdmin, VS Code/Notepad++
##Key Fields
- id – Auto-increment PK
- username – Login identifier
- email – Verification + notifications
- phone – Contact/MFA channel
- subscription – Service tier
- payment_plan – Billing configuration 
##Quick Start
- Install XAMPP → Start Apache + MySQL
- phpMyAdmin → Create aami_db + users table
- htdocs → Drop index.html + process.php
- localhost/aami → Experience branded AAMI form
##Learning Outcomes
- AAMI-branded UI/UX with enterprise color scheme + logo
- End-to-end CRUD insertion workflow
- PHP sanitization + SQL injection prevention
- Production SQL fundamentals through secure operations
- XAMPP mastery for LAMP development
